@page "/docs/validation"

<PageTitle>Docs_Validation.razor</PageTitle>

<h1>Docs_Validation.razor</h1>

<div class="docsection">1. Validation Concept</div>
<p>
	There are 3 Validation properties for &lt;CoreUploader&gt;
</p>
<ul>
	<li><a href="/demo/maxsizekb">MaxSizeKB</a></li>
	<li><a href="/demo/acceptextensions">AcceptMimeTypes</a></li>
	<li><a href="/demo/acceptfileexts">AcceptExtensions</a></li>
</ul>
<p>
	If files don't match the properties, the CoreUploader.FilesError event will be fired.
</p>
<p>
	If both AcceptMimeTypes and AcceptExtensions are set, the files only need match one of them.
</p>
<p>
	AcceptMimeTypes and AcceptExtensions will work for Most browsers and the selected file dialog will hide invalid files.
</p>

<div class="docsection">2. MinSizeKB/MaxSizeKB (in bytes)</div>
<p>
	This property sets the maximum allowed size of the file, in bytes.
	set MaxSizeKB="200" means 200KB.
</p>


<div class="docsection">3. AcceptMimeTypes</div>
<p>
	This property can be set to one or multiple values like this :
	AcceptMimeTypes="image/*,video/*"
</p>

<div class="docsection">4. AcceptExtensions</div>
<p>
	This property can be set to one or multiple values like this :
	AcceptExtensions="doc,docx,xls,xlsx,ppt,pptx,zip"
</p>

<div class="docsection">5. Custom Validation before upload</div>
<p>
	Developer can modify HandleFilesAdded to put invalid files to ErrFiles.
</p>

<div class="docsection">6. Custom Validation after upload</div>
<p>
	Developer can modify ProcessFilesAsync to check file content after file be uploaded.
</p>

